-- Taiwanese Stocks: Acer, ILI Technology Corp., Microbio, Rexchip
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-07-03T06:10:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/taiwanese-stocks-acer-ili-technology-corp-microbio-rexchip.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The  Taiex Index (TWSE)  rose 1 percent to 7,418.36, its highest
close since May 10.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT), Taiwanâ€™s largest computer maker, added
0.8 percent to NT$31.15. The company said it plans to buy back
10 million shares at between NT$28 and NT$35 each from now to
Sept. 2.  ILI Technology Corp. (3598)  (3598 TT), a manufacturer of display
drivers, gained 2.5 percent to NT$82.5. The company said
unconsolidated sales rose 62 percent from a year earlier to
NT$885.4 million ($29.6 million) in June.  Microbio Co. (4128)  (4128 TT), a drugmaker, slipped 2.2 percent to
NT$37.25. The company said unconsolidated sales in June fell 39
percent to NT$32.78 million.  Rexchip Electronics Corp. (4932)  (4932 TT), a venture with
bankrupt Japanese chipmaker Elpida Memory Inc., advanced 10
percent to NT$11.04, the highest close since Feb. 15.  Powerchip
Technology Corp. (5346)  (5346 TT), a maker of memory chips, and a unit
agreed to sell 691 million shares in Rexchip to Micron
Technology Inc. for NT$9.7 billion. Powerchip jumped 6.9 percent
to NT$0.62.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
